<subSubSection id="C35C9886FFFDFF990380FE31FDF44C41" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph id="8BF9CB0DFFFDFF990380FE31FC264F8C" blockId="30.[120,1225,415,1786]" box="[168,1018,415,441]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
<typeStatus id="54FD75AFFFFDFF990380FE31FF3E4F8C" box="[168,226,415,441]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">TYPE</typeStatus>
SPECIES: 
<taxonomicName id="4C46B08EFFFDFF99027AFE0EFD034F8C" authority="McKenzie, 1942" authorityName="McKenzie" authorityYear="1942" box="[338,735,415,441]" class="Insecta" family="Margarodidae" genus="Pityococcus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ferrisi">
<emphasis id="B932171FFFFDFF99027AFE0EFDC74F8C" box="[338,539,415,441]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Pityococcus ferrisi</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFD7B6FCFFFDFF99010BFE31FD034F8C" author="McKenzie, H. L." box="[547,735,415,441]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" pagination="1 - 18" refId="ref37954" refString="McKenzie, H. L. 1942. New species of pine-infesting Margarodidae from California and southwestern United States (Homoptera; Coccoidea; Margarodidae). Microentomology 7: 1 - 18." type="journal article" year="1942">McKenzie, 1942</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
; by original designation.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF9CB0DFFFDFF990380FE6AFDF44C41" blockId="30.[120,1225,415,1786]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
GENERIC DIAGNOSIS (macropterous male): Based on the description of 
<taxonomicName id="4C46B08EFFFDFF9900D4FE6BFB7B4FEA" box="[1020,1191,453,479]" class="Insecta" family="Margarodidae" genus="Pityococcus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="B932171FFFFDFF9900D4FE6BFBA24FEB" box="[1020,1150,453,478]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Pityococcus</emphasis>
sp.
</taxonomicName>
in 
<bibRefCitation id="EFD7B6FCFFFDFF990350FE47FE714C31" author="Hodgson, C. J. &amp; I. Foldi" box="[120,429,489,516]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" pagination="1 - 250" refId="ref36707" refString="Hodgson, C. J., and I. Foldi. 2006. A review of the Margarodidae sensu Morrison (Hemiptera: Coccoidea) and some related taxa based on the morphology of adult males. Zootaxa 1263: 1 - 250." type="journal article" year="2006">Hodgson and Foldi (2006)</bibRefCitation>
and the present description, 
<taxonomicName id="4C46B08EFFFDFF99002BFE44FC584C36" authorityName="McKenzie" authorityYear="1942" box="[771,900,490,515]" class="Insecta" family="Margarodidae" genus="Pityococcus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B932171FFFFDFF99002BFE44FC584C36" box="[771,900,490,515]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Pityococcus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from the fossil 
<taxonomicName id="4C46B08EFFFDFF9907A7FE44FE384C1C" authority="Koteja, 1988 c" authorityName="Koteja" authorityYear="1988" class="Insecta" family="Hemiptera (awaiting allocation)" genus="Cancerococcus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="apterus">
<emphasis id="B932171FFFFDFF9907A7FE44FE994C1C" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Cancerococcus apterus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFD7B6FCFFFDFF990263FDA1FE384C1C" author="Koteja, J." box="[331,484,527,553]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" pagination="405 - 416" refId="ref37331" refString="Koteja, J. 1988 c. Two new eriococcids from Baltic amber (Homoptera, Coccinea). Deutsche Entomologische Zeitschrift 35: 405 - 416." type="journal article" year="1988">Koteja, 1988c</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="4C46B08EFFFDFF9902DCFDBEFD544C1C" authorityName="F. Brand" authorityYear="1925" box="[500,648,528,553]" class="Trebouxiophyceae" family="Prasiolaceae" genus="Desmococcus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Prasiolales" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Chlorophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B932171FFFFDFF9902DCFDBEFD544C1C" box="[500,648,528,553]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Desmococcus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
male is unknown) with the following combination of characters: ocular sclerite with five pairs of simple eyes (vs. four in 
<taxonomicName id="4C46B08EFFFDFF9900ECFD9BFBB54C7A" authorityName="Koteja" authorityYear="1988" box="[964,1129,565,591]" class="Insecta" family="Hemiptera (awaiting allocation)" genus="Cancerococcus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B932171FFFFDFF9900ECFD9BFBB54C7A" box="[964,1129,565,591]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Cancerococcus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), wings present (vs. absent in 
<taxonomicName id="4C46B08EFFFDFF99025CFDF4FDCB4C41" authorityName="Koteja" authorityYear="1988" box="[372,535,602,628]" class="Insecta" family="Hemiptera (awaiting allocation)" genus="Cancerococcus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B932171FFFFDFF99025CFDF4FDCB4C41" box="[372,535,602,628]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Cancerococcus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C35C9886FFFDFF990380FDD1FE044D1A" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BF9CB0DFFFDFF990380FDD1FB454CAC" blockId="30.[120,1225,415,1786]" box="[168,1177,639,665]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">OCCURRENCE: Recent species distributed in the Nearctic. Fossil species in Baltic amber.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF9CB0DFFFDFF990380FD0AFE044D1A" blockId="30.[120,1225,415,1786]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
SPECIES INCLUDED: 
<taxonomicName id="4C46B08EFFFDFF99028AFD0BFDF54C8B" authorityName="McKenzie" authorityYear="1942" box="[418,553,677,702]" class="Insecta" family="Margarodidae" genus="Pityococcus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B932171FFFFDFF99028AFD0BFDF54C8B" box="[418,553,677,702]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Pityococcus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was defined based on adult female morphology and includes the Recent 
<taxonomicName id="4C46B08EFFFDFF99025AFD64FD6E4CD1" authority="McKenzie, 1942" authorityName="McKenzie" authorityYear="1942" box="[370,690,713,740]" class="Insecta" family="Margarodidae" genus="Pityococcus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="deleoni">
<emphasis id="B932171FFFFDFF99025AFD64FE3F4CD6" box="[370,483,713,739]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">P. deleoni</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFD7B6FCFFFDFF9902C6FD67FD6E4CD1" author="McKenzie, H. L." box="[494,690,713,740]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" pagination="1 - 18" refId="ref37954" refString="McKenzie, H. L. 1942. New species of pine-infesting Margarodidae from California and southwestern United States (Homoptera; Coccoidea; Margarodidae). Microentomology 7: 1 - 18." type="journal article" year="1942">McKenzie, 1942</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C46B08EFFFDFF9901E9FD64FC2F4CD1" authority="McKenzie, 1942" authorityName="McKenzie" authorityYear="1942" box="[705,1011,713,740]" class="Insecta" family="Margarodidae" genus="Pityococcus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ferrisi">
<emphasis id="B932171FFFFDFF9901E9FD64FCF84CD1" box="[705,804,714,740]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">P. ferrisi</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFD7B6FCFFFDFF990007FD67FC2F4CD1" author="McKenzie, H. L." box="[815,1011,713,740]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" pagination="1 - 18" refId="ref37954" refString="McKenzie, H. L. 1942. New species of pine-infesting Margarodidae from California and southwestern United States (Homoptera; Coccoidea; Margarodidae). Microentomology 7: 1 - 18." type="journal article" year="1942">McKenzie, 1942</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="4C46B08EFFFDFF990712FD64FEEE4D3C" authority="McKenzie, 1942" authorityName="McKenzie" authorityYear="1942" class="Insecta" family="Margarodidae" genus="Pityococcus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rugulosus">
<emphasis id="B932171FFFFDFF990712FD64FB144CD6" box="[1082,1224,713,739]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">P. rugulosus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFD7B6FCFFFDFF990350FD41FEEE4D3C" author="McKenzie, H. L." box="[120,306,751,777]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" pagination="1 - 18" refId="ref37954" refString="McKenzie, H. L. 1942. New species of pine-infesting Margarodidae from California and southwestern United States (Homoptera; Coccoidea; Margarodidae). Microentomology 7: 1 - 18." type="journal article" year="1942">McKenzie, 1942</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. Only an unidentified 
<taxonomicName id="4C46B08EFFFDFF99011FFD5EFD654D3C" authorityName="McKenzie" authorityYear="1942" box="[567,697,752,777]" class="Insecta" family="Margarodidae" genus="Pityococcus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B932171FFFFDFF99011FFD5EFD654D3C" box="[567,697,752,777]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Pityococcus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described based on a macropterous male in 
<bibRefCitation id="EFD7B6FCFFFDFF9903B0FCBAFE0F4D1A" author="Hodgson, C. J. &amp; I. Foldi" box="[152,467,788,815]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" pagination="1 - 250" refId="ref36707" refString="Hodgson, C. J., and I. Foldi. 2006. A review of the Margarodidae sensu Morrison (Hemiptera: Coccoidea) and some related taxa based on the morphology of adult males. Zootaxa 1263: 1 - 250." type="journal article" year="2006">Hodgson and Foldi (2006)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C35C9886FFFDFF990380FC94FD5D48CF" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BF9CB0DFFFDFF990380FC94FCFB4AFC" blockId="30.[120,1225,415,1786]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
COMMENTS: Adult males of 
<taxonomicName id="4C46B08EFFFDFF9902C6FC94FDB34D66" authorityName="McKenzie" authorityYear="1942" box="[494,623,826,851]" class="Insecta" family="Margarodidae" genus="Pityococcus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B932171FFFFDFF9902C6FC94FDB34D66" box="[494,623,826,851]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Pityococcus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have been frequently found as inclusions in Eocene ambers and, according to 
<bibRefCitation id="EFD7B6FCFFFDFF99029DFCF1FDB94D4C" author="Koteja, J." box="[437,613,863,889]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" pagination="187 - 218" refId="ref37502" refString="Koteja, J. 2000 a. Advances in the study of fossil coccids (Hemiptera: Coccinea). Polskie Pismo Entomologiczne 69: 187 - 218." type="journal article" year="2000">Koteja (2000a)</bibRefCitation>
, all are apterous. Therefore, this is the first formal description of a winged 
<taxonomicName id="4C46B08EFFFDFF9902A4FC2BFDD14DAB" authorityName="McKenzie" authorityYear="1942" box="[396,525,901,926]" class="Insecta" family="Margarodidae" genus="Pityococcus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B932171FFFFDFF9902A4FC2BFDD14DAB" box="[396,525,901,926]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Pityococcus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
male in the fossil record. There are currently three described extant 
<taxonomicName id="4C46B08EFFFDFF9903EEFC04FEA34DF1" box="[198,383,938,964]" class="Insecta" family="Margarodidae" genus="Pityococcus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="B932171FFFFDFF9903EEFC04FE9B4DF6" box="[198,327,938,963]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Pityococcus</emphasis>
spp.
</taxonomicName>
, all of which are based on adult females. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFD7B6FCFFFDFF990074FC07FB524DF1" author="Hodgson, C. J. &amp; I. Foldi" box="[860,1166,937,964]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" pagination="1 - 250" refId="ref36707" refString="Hodgson, C. J., and I. Foldi. 2006. A review of the Margarodidae sensu Morrison (Hemiptera: Coccoidea) and some related taxa based on the morphology of adult males. Zootaxa 1263: 1 - 250." type="journal article" year="2006">Hodgson and Foldi (2006)</bibRefCitation>
provided the only description of a macropterous male 
<taxonomicName id="4C46B08EFFFDFF9901E4FC7EFC914DDC" authorityName="McKenzie" authorityYear="1942" box="[716,845,976,1001]" class="Insecta" family="Margarodidae" genus="Pityococcus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B932171FFFFDFF9901E4FC7EFC914DDC" box="[716,845,976,1001]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Pityococcus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but unidentified to species. The same authors also mentioned a specimen of 
<taxonomicName id="4C46B08EFFFDFF990143FC5BFD374A3B" authorityName="McKenzie" authorityYear="1942" box="[619,747,1013,1038]" class="Insecta" family="Margarodidae" genus="Pityococcus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B932171FFFFDFF990143FC5BFD374A3B" box="[619,747,1013,1038]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Pityococcus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
labeled as 
<taxonomicName id="4C46B08EFFFDFF99004CFC5BFC104A3B" authorityName="McKenzie" authorityYear="1942" box="[868,972,1012,1038]" class="Insecta" family="Margarodidae" genus="Pityococcus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="deleoni">
<emphasis id="B932171FFFFDFF99004CFC5BFC104A3B" box="[868,972,1012,1038]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">P. deleoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but most appendages were missing. 
<emphasis id="B932171FFFFDFF990231FBB4FD954A06" box="[281,585,1049,1075]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
<taxonomicName id="4C46B08EFFFDFF990231FBB4FD994A06" authority="Vea &amp; Grimaldi, 2015" authorityName="Vea &amp; Grimaldi" authorityYear="2015" box="[281,581,1049,1075]" class="Insecta" family="Margarodidae" genus="Pityococcus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="moniliformalis" status="n. sp.">Pityococcus moniliformalis</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A201AA64FFFDFF990167FBB4FD504A01" box="[591,652,1050,1076]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, was assigned in this genus based on the following combination of characters: ocular sclerite with a row of five simple eyes; antennae bearing short, stout, fleshy setae; the presence of capitate setae; the presence of a membranous area on the scutum; the quadrangular shape of the scutellum, with anterior margin shorter than posterior margin, and the presence of ostioles on abdominal segment VI.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF9CB0DFFFDFF990380FB7BFD4048BF" blockId="30.[120,1225,415,1786]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
In our cladogram, 
<taxonomicName id="4C46B08EFFFDFF9902A9FB7BFDE34ADB" authorityName="Vea &amp; Grimaldi" authorityYear="2015" box="[385,575,1236,1262]" class="Insecta" family="Margarodidae" genus="Pityococcus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="moniliformalis">
<emphasis id="B932171FFFFDFF9902A9FB7BFDE34ADB" box="[385,575,1236,1262]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">P. moniliformalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is retrieved as the sister taxon to the Recent 
<taxonomicName id="4C46B08EFFFDFF99076FFB7BFF4B4B21" class="Insecta" family="Margarodidae" genus="Pityococcus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="B932171FFFFDFF99076FFB7BFB144ADB" box="[1095,1224,1237,1262]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Pityococcus</emphasis>
sp.
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C46B08EFFFDFF9903F9FB54FEAC4B21" authorityName="McKenzie" authorityYear="1942" box="[209,368,1274,1300]" class="Insecta" family="Pityococcidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Pityococcidae</taxonomicName>
is included in an extinct lineage including 
<taxonomicName id="4C46B08EFFFDFF990049FB54FC2F4B26" authorityName="Koteja" authorityYear="2000" box="[865,1011,1274,1299]" class="Insecta" family="Hemiptera (awaiting allocation)" genus="Turonicoccus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B932171FFFFDFF990049FB54FC2F4B26" box="[865,1011,1274,1299]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Turonicoccus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis id="B932171FFFFDFF990729FB54FB764B21" box="[1025,1194,1274,1300]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
<taxonomicName id="4C46B08EFFFDFF990729FB54FB7A4B21" authority="Vea &amp; Grimaldi, 2015" authorityName="Vea &amp; Grimaldi" authorityYear="2015" box="[1025,1190,1274,1300]" class="Insecta" family="Hemiptera incertae sedis" genus="Pedicellicoccus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="n. gen.">Pedicellicoccus</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A201AA64FFFDFF990799FB54FF754B0C" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" rank="genus">n. gen.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C46B08EFFFDFF99039BFAB1FEE34B0C" box="[179,319,1311,1337]" class="Insecta" family="Hemiptera (awaiting allocation)" genus="Grimaldiella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B932171FFFFDFF99039BFAB1FEE34B0C" box="[179,319,1311,1337]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Grimaldiella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="4C46B08EFFFDFF990255FAB1FDD34B0C" authorityName="Beardsley" authorityYear="1969" box="[381,527,1311,1337]" class="Insecta" family="Hemiptera (awaiting allocation)" genus="Electrococcus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B932171FFFFDFF990255FAB1FDD34B0C" box="[381,527,1311,1337]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Electrococcus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Koteja discussed the affinity of 
<taxonomicName id="4C46B08EFFFDFF990052FA8EFBD74B0C" authorityName="Koteja" authorityYear="2000" box="[890,1035,1312,1337]" class="Insecta" family="Hemiptera (awaiting allocation)" genus="Turonicoccus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B932171FFFFDFF990052FA8EFBD74B0C" box="[890,1035,1312,1337]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Turonicoccus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C46B08EFFFDFF99076AFA8EFB1D4B0C" authorityName="McKenzie" authorityYear="1942" box="[1090,1217,1312,1337]" class="Insecta" family="Margarodidae" genus="Pityococcus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B932171FFFFDFF99076AFA8EFB1D4B0C" box="[1090,1217,1312,1337]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Pityococcus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, with regard to the presence of an everted endophallus (
<bibRefCitation id="EFD7B6FCFFFDFF9901D2FAEAFC0A4B6A" author="Koteja, J." box="[762,982,1348,1375]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" pagination="147 - 229" refId="ref37531" refString="Koteja, J. 2000 b. Scale insects (Homoptera, Coccinea) from Upper Cretaceous New Jersey amber. In D. A. Grimaldi (editor), Studies on fossils in amber, with particular reference to the Cretaceous of New Jersey: 147 - 229. Leiden: Backhuys Publishers." type="book chapter" year="2000">Koteja, 2000b: 176</bibRefCitation>
), found for the most part in archaeococcoids with compound eyes (
<bibRefCitation id="EFD7B6FCFFFDFF9901B0FAC4FC1A4BB1" author="Hodgson, C. J. &amp; I. Foldi" box="[664,966,1385,1412]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" pagination="1 - 250" refId="ref36707" refString="Hodgson, C. J., and I. Foldi. 2006. A review of the Margarodidae sensu Morrison (Hemiptera: Coccoidea) and some related taxa based on the morphology of adult males. Zootaxa 1263: 1 - 250." type="journal article" year="2006">Hodgson and Foldi, 2006</bibRefCitation>
). However, Koteja did not have a detailed description of Recent 
<taxonomicName id="4C46B08EFFFDFF99014FFA3EFD344B9C" authorityName="McKenzie" authorityYear="1942" box="[615,744,1424,1449]" class="Insecta" family="Margarodidae" genus="Pityococcus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B932171FFFFDFF99014FFA3EFD344B9C" box="[615,744,1424,1449]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Pityococcus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
at the time, having found only apterous 
<taxonomicName id="4C46B08EFFFDFF990350FA1BFF254BFB" authorityName="McKenzie" authorityYear="1942" box="[120,249,1461,1486]" class="Insecta" family="Margarodidae" genus="Pityococcus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B932171FFFFDFF990350FA1BFF254BFB" box="[120,249,1461,1486]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Pityococcus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in Baltic amber, and relying on the reports of 
<bibRefCitation id="EFD7B6FCFFFDFF99002AFA1AFBC44BFB" author="Miller, D. R. &amp; G. L. Miller" box="[770,1048,1460,1486]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" pagination="1 - 35" refId="ref38051" refString="Miller, D. R., and G. L. Miller. 1993. A new species of Puto and preliminary analysis of the phylogenetic position of the Puto group within the Coccoidea (Homoptera: Pseudococcidae). Jeffersoniana 4: 1 - 35." type="journal article" year="1993">Miller and Miller (1993)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="EFD7B6FCFFFDFF990767FA1AFEFD4BC1" author="Miller, D. R. &amp; M. E. Gimpel" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" pagination="212 - 218" refId="ref37988" refString="Miller, D. R., and M. E. Gimpel. 1999. New combinations, new synonymy, and homonomy in the Eriococcidae, new homonymy and synonymy in the Cerococcidae, and transfer of Cancerococcus Koteja to the Margarodidae (Hemiptera: Coccoidea). Proceedings of the Entomological Society of Washington 101: 212 - 218." type="journal article" year="1999">Miller and Gimpel (1999)</bibRefCitation>
for Recent representatives of the genus. Given current knowledge, 
<taxonomicName id="4C46B08EFFFDFF990705FA74FB724BC6" authorityName="McKenzie" authorityYear="1942" box="[1069,1198,1498,1523]" class="Insecta" family="Margarodidae" genus="Pityococcus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B932171FFFFDFF990705FA74FB724BC6" box="[1069,1198,1498,1523]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Pityococcus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is mostly closely related to 
<taxonomicName id="4C46B08EFFFDFF9902B3F9AEFDF2482C" authorityName="Koteja" authorityYear="2000" box="[411,558,1536,1561]" class="Insecta" family="Hemiptera (awaiting allocation)" genus="Turonicoccus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B932171FFFFDFF9902B3F9AEFDF2482C" box="[411,558,1536,1561]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Turonicoccus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
based on the presence of the endophallus, antennal segments with short and stout fleshy setae, capitate setae on the apical antennal segment (but 
<taxonomicName id="4C46B08EFFFDFF9907A0F98BFF0A4856" authorityName="Koteja" authorityYear="2000" class="Insecta" family="Hemiptera (awaiting allocation)" genus="Turonicoccus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B932171FFFFDFF9907A0F98BFF0A4856" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Turonicoccus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
also bears capitate setae on other antennal segments), but differs by having only five simple eyes (as opposed to six in 
<taxonomicName id="4C46B08EFFFDFF9902D1F9DEFD5748BC" authorityName="Koteja" authorityYear="2000" box="[505,651,1648,1673]" class="Insecta" family="Hemiptera (awaiting allocation)" genus="Turonicoccus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B932171FFFFDFF9902D1F9DEFD5748BC" box="[505,651,1648,1673]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Turonicoccus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF9CB0DFFFDFF990380F93AFD5D48CF" blockId="30.[120,1225,415,1786]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
All Recent 
<taxonomicName id="4C46B08EFFFDFF99020DF93BFE7A489B" authorityName="McKenzie" authorityYear="1942" box="[293,422,1685,1710]" class="Insecta" family="Margarodidae" genus="Pityococcus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B932171FFFFDFF99020DF93BFE7A489B" box="[293,422,1685,1710]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Pityococcus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are distributed in the Nearctic region and feed on pine trees. The presence of 
<taxonomicName id="4C46B08EFFFDFF9903F8F914FE8D48E6" authorityName="McKenzie" authorityYear="1942" box="[208,337,1722,1747]" class="Insecta" family="Margarodidae" genus="Pityococcus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B932171FFFFDFF9903F8F914FE8D48E6" box="[208,337,1722,1747]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Pityococcus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in Palaearctic Baltic ambers indicates that this genus is a relict taxon that was probably more widely distributed in the past.
</paragraph>
